  "full_response": "We are asked to construct the rank-2 contravariant tensor  \n\nT^{ab} = \u20136\\,v^{a}u^{b}\n\nfrom the given contravariant 4\u2013vectors (all components are quoted in the same inertial frame R):\n\nv^{a} = (v^{0},v^{1},v^{2},v^{3}) = (5,\\; -1,\\; 0,\\; 1)  \nu^{b} = (u^{0},u^{1},u^{2},u^{3}) = (-2,\\; 1,\\; 1,\\; -6)\n\nSince T^{ab} is simply the outer product of v^{a} and u^{b} multiplied by the scalar \u20136, each component is\n\nT^{ab}= -6\\,v^{a}\\,u^{b}\\qquad(a,b = 0,1,2,3).\n\nCompute each row (fixed a) in turn.\n\n1. a = 0 \u2003(v^{0}=5):\n\nT^{0b}= -6(5)u^{b}= -30\\,u^{b}\n\u2003\u2192 T^{00} = -30(-2)= 60  \n\u2003\u2003T^{01} = -30(1)= -30  \n\u2003\u2003T^{02} = -30(1)= -30  \n\u2003\u2003T^{03} = -30(-6)= 180\n\n2. a = 1 \u2003(v^{1} = \u20131):\n\nT^{1b}= -6(-1)u^{b}= +6\\,u^{b}\n\u2003\u2192 T^{10} = 6(-2)= -12  \n\u2003\u2003T^{11} = 6(1)= 6  \n\u2003\u2003T^{12} = 6(1)= 6  \n\u2003\u2003T^{13} = 6(-6)= -36\n\n3. a = 2 \u2003(v^{2}=0):\n\nT^{2b}=0 \\quad\u21d2\\quad T^{20}=T^{21}=T^{22}=T^{23}=0\n\n4. a = 3 \u2003(v^{3}=1):\n\nT^{3b}= -6(1)u^{b}= -6\\,u^{b}\n\u2003\u2192 T^{30} = -6(-2)= 12  \n\u2003\u2003T^{31} = -6(1)= -6  \n\u2003\u2003T^{32} = -6(1)= -6  \n\u2003\u2003T^{33} = -6(-6)= 36\n\nCollecting everything, the matrix of components T^{ab} (= \u20136v^{a}u^{b}) is\n\n            b = 0     1     2     3\n   a = 0   [ 60   -30   -30   180 ]\n   a = 1   [ -12    6     6   -36 ]\n   a = 2   [  0     0     0     0 ]\n   a = 3   [ 12    -6    -6    36 ]\n\n\\boxed{\\;\nT^{ab} = -6\\,v^{a}u^{b} =\n\\begin{pmatrix}\n 60 & -30 & -30 & 180\\\\\n-12 &   6  &   6 & -36\\\\\n  0 &   0  &   0 &   0\\\\\n 12 &  -6  &  -6 &  36\n\\end{pmatrix}\n\\;}\n\nConfidence: 93%",
